15. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:143855" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pseudomyrma flavidula Smith" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidula">Pseudomyrma flavidula</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="157" pageNumber="157" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="157" pageNumber="157">
Worker. Length 2 3/4 lines.-Entirely smooth and shining yellow: the eyes and tips of the mandibles black; the head broader than in 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:188085" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pseudomyrma pallida Smith" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="157" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida">P. pallida</taxonomicName>
, which it much resembles; a very faintly impressed line runs from the anterior stemma to the clypeus, which has a deeper impressed pit in the middle. Thorax strangulated in the middle. Abdomen covered with a fine silky pile; more or less fuscous at the apex, and with a fuscous spot, more or less distinct, on each side at the base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="157" pageNumber="157" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="157" pageNumber="157">Hab. Brazil (Santarem).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
